    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="107"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.24/107</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by Mr. Vernon L. Phelps of the
                        Division of Commercial Policy and Agreements</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-15">May 15,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell rendition="#top #nowrap">Participants:</cell>
                        <cell>Mr. Caldwell,<note n="16" xml:id="d107fn16">John K.Caldwell.</note>
                            American Minister to Ethiopia</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. Walker—OLLA<note n="17" xml:id="d107fn17">Office of Lend-Lease
                                Administration.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. Phelps—TA</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. Deressa, Vice Minister of Finance of Ethiopia</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. Ababa, Ethiopia</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. Tesamma, Ethiopia</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>The Minister brought Mr. Deressa and his colleagues in to discuss certain matters
                    regarding lend-lease assistance to Ethiopia. Mr. Deressa presented a full power
                    authorizing him to conclude with this Government any lend-lease agreement and to
                    sign on behalf of the Ethiopian Government everything so agreed upon.</p>
                <p>He was given a copy of the usual form of representations required by Sections 4
                    and 7 of the Act,<note n="18" xml:id="d107fn18">Approved March 11, 1941; 55
                        Stat. 31.</note> and he agreed to prepare and submit these
                    representations.</p>
                <p>It was explained that the text of a master lend-lease agreement was in
                    preparation and that it would probably be ready for his consideration upon his
                    return to Washington from the Food Conference<note n="19" xml:id="d107fn19"
                        >United Nations Conference on Food and Agriculture at Hot Springs, Virginia,
                        May 18–June 3; for correspondence, see <ref target="frus1943v01#pg_820">vol.
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 820</ref> ff.</note>
                    <pb facs="0108" n="96" xml:id="pg_96"/> which he and his colleagues are
                    attending as representatives of the Ethiopian Government.</p>
                <p>Mr. Deressa stated that he had a list of articles which his Government desired to
                    obtain under lend-lease which he will submit later. Mr. Walker explained to Mr.
                    Deressa that we would be glad to give sympathetic consideration to the list,
                    subject of course to the overall supply and shipping situation. Mr. Deressa was
                    given no encouragement that any large amount of lend-lease assistance might be
                    forthcoming soon.</p>
                <p>As background information, a copy of the <hi rend="italic">Seventh Report to
                        Congress on Lend-Lease Operations</hi> was given to Mr. Deressa.</p>
            </div>
